data.description: LAFAYETTE SEEKERS!!!!  UPDATES SINCE LISTING:  New laminate wood flooring in primary bedroom.  HVAC has been serviced and home has a home inspection for review by a a licensed home inspector.  Front and back yards have been refreshed.  Come home to this inviting 2300+ sq foot Acadian style home located on a dead end street. The covered front porch adds to the classic charm of the Acadian design. and offers a comfortable spot to relax, admire the beauty of the Oak Tree, enjoy the outdoors or engage in conversation with neighbors. The heart of the home, the kitchen, is spacious with an abundant of counter space and cabinets and an attractive wooden ceiling inset to add a cozy and warm feel. A breakfast area conveniently located next to kitchen, for those morning meals and coffee. More... Need a formal dining area? An amazing space located off kitchen is the perfect place. Adjacent to this room is a great den with a wood burning fireplace, pretty laminate floors and large windows that let in natural lighting, All bedrooms are roomy with nice closet space. For outdoor lovers, a screen porch overlooks the large fenced in back yard. AND, a great patio area and existing flower beds just waiting for your own personal garden touches. Overall, this 2300 square foot Acadian-style home is a perfect blend of classic charm. With its large living spaces, great kitchen, and dining area, and inviting outdoor living, it offers a wonderful place to call home for those seeking comfort, style, and a sense of community in a tranquil setting. This home and property is located conveniently to Costco, a new Rouses Market and upcoming Top Golf.
